[1]
Date: 14 May 2005
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: WHO CSR [13 May 2005]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_05_13/en/index.html>

Suspected acute haemorrhagic fever in the Republic of the Congo 13 May 2005
----------------------------------
Between 27 Apr [2005] and 11 May 2005, 9 suspected cases of acute
haemorrhagic fever have been reported in Etoumbi (8) and Mbomo (1) in
Cuvette Ouest Region. All cases have been fatal. A total of 52 contacts are
being monitored in Etoumbi and Mbomo.
The Ministry of Health, the WHO Regional Office for Africa, and Medecins
Sans Frontieres-Holland are in the field to assess the situation and to
collect clinical samples for diagnosis. These will be tested by the Centre
International de Recherches Medicales de Franceville (CIRMF), Gabon.
--
